// parsePseudo
// Parses raw pseudo-file text into a structured object of header metadata and function blocks.
// synced: 2026-03-26T00:00:00Z

Types exported: CallsRef { name, fileStem }, ParsedFunction { name, params, returnType, isExport, updatedAt, calls, body }, ParsedPseudo { titleLine, subtitleLine, syncedAt, moduleProse, functions }.

FUNCTION parsePseudo(content) -> ParsedPseudo [2026-03-26]                EXPORT
  Parses a full pseudo-file string into structured data.
  IF content is empty, RETURN a zero-value ParsedPseudo with all fields empty.
  Split content into lines. Walk leading // lines: first becomes titleLine, second subtitleLine, any further // line matching "synced: <ISO>" sets syncedAt.
  Collect non-// lines before the first FUNCTION keyword as moduleProse.
  Walk remaining lines: when a FUNCTION header line matches the regex, extract name, params, returnType, isExport flag, and updatedAt date. Collect body lines until a "---" separator. Call parseCallsFromBody on the body to populate calls. Append the resulting ParsedFunction.
  RETURN assembled ParsedPseudo.

---

FUNCTION parseCallsFromBody(body) -> CallsRef[]
  Internal helper. Scans body lines for any line starting with "CALLS:".
  FOR each such line, runs a regex to extract all name(fileStem) pairs and pushes them to the result array.
  RETURN the collected CallsRef array.
